  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Family Welfare Through Minor Livestock Raising in the Mexteca Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Improving Family Welfare through Minor Livestock Raising in the Mixteca Region project will support 72 families in four communities in the Mixteca Alta region, state of Oaxaca, southern Mexico. The population faces poverty, unemployment, under-nutrition, advanced soil erosion and low food production. The families will receive 310 sheep, two cows, six hogs, 26 goats, 170 hens, 22 native beehives, 70 pounds of vegetable seeds and 20 fruit trees. The rural families can improve their family nutrition by producing meat, eggs, milk, honey, vegetables and fruit. They will also sell surplus produce at local markets to generate income and improve their quality of life. Another 144 families will benefit from Passing on the Gift.</narrative>
  </description>
